HEADWORD: Lobbyist
<hw>Lob"by*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of the lobby; a person
who solicits members of a legislature for the purpose of influencing
legislation.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

